Prions are infectious proteins that are able to propagate an altered conformational state (Prusiner, 1982<IMG BORDER=1 WIDTH=8 HEIGHT=7 ALT="Go"
SRC="/icons/fig-down.gif">). The term was coined to designate the infectious elements responsible for spongiform encephalopathies in mammals, a group of fatal neurodegenerative affections that include Creutzfeldt-Jacob disease in humans and mad-cow disease
